I gave you a 3 because although your app is great, there are 6 important 
improvements that need to happen for me to give you a 5 (which I am happy 
to do if these improvements are met): 1) Regarding the Calendar View Tab: 
Our mood changes throughout the day, yet in calendar view, there is no way 
to distinguish the chronological order in which you felt which mood. It 
would be EXTREMELY handy if you found a way to display the mood that users 
logged IN THE ORDER that they log them in. i.e, if I felt hopeful in the 
morning, sad in the afternoon and peaceful in the evening, then the emojis 
should be displayed in that order. Unfortunately you have everything set up 
so that the order of moods appear (left to right) in the order that appear 
in the list of moods (from top to bottom), so on the calendar it looks like 
I was peaceful, frustrated THEN hopeful... not accurate at all. This is bad 
because when you look back at your calendar at the end of the week, it 
looks like you started/ended the days with emotions that you didn't 
experience in those ways. 2) Regarding the emoji list under "Mood" More 
mood emojis, PLEASE! Including: - the opposite of "sweet passion" like 
perhaps "not in the mood" or "dispassionate" - "confident" - "strong" - 
"weak" - "assertive" - "limitless" - "disconnected" - "focused" 3) 
Regarding user interface/display while inputting data for an individual 
day: Please add two more displayed lines of text to the top of the page. 
(Right now it only displays one tiny line, when three, four or even five 
tiny lines could easily and aesthetically fit). I have Samsung galaxy 9, so 
maybe my aspect ratio allows WAY more lines to be there than for other 
smartphones... Either way, at least 2 extra lines can fit, even on a 
smaller screen. Please make this small change!) 4) Regarding the calendar 
wheel tab view: PLEASE find a way to have multiple months appear on there 
at a time. Perhaps in a spiral fashion? For those of us with extra long 
cycles (say of 36 days) or irregular periods (having each cycle last 
between 7 and 60+ days), it would really help to see how the cycles look 
over a larger period of time, say 3 or even 6 months. This could be 
accomplished with having concentric circles nested within each other, with 
one circle representing one month, allowed the user to see THE BIG PICTURE 
of how her period looks over several months. Currently, seeing just one 
month at a time ruins the effect of seeing the period as a continuous cycle 
(it's basically no different than calendar view, which is a shame because 
that's part of what we're paying for by going "Pro." 5) One last 
improvement for Calendar wheel tab: It would be AMAZING if you could even 
allow the user to adjust the diameter of the circles (or spiral) to reflect 
that woman's individual cycle length, whether that be a lunar 28 days, 
less, or more. That way, users can visualize their period as a truly cyclic 
phenomenon, moving forward and backward in time... and really show how 
their unique pattern unfolds!!! That would be soooooo cool! 6) Regarding 
moon phases: They are missing from the calendar view. A few basic moon 
phase emojis üåöüåíüåìüåîüåùüåñüåóüåò would do the trick! All that said, I am 
almost completely satisfied with this app. It's perfect for tracking my 
period, and in fact already goes above and beyond by allowing me to log the 
many experiences related to my period. I'm SO grateful for that!
